&gt;Subtract sale price from original price to determine the discount amount. Next, divide the discount amount by original price. Convert this decimal amount into a percentage. This percent is the discount rate. For an example, a lamp shows a discount price of $30 with an original price of $50. $50 - $30 = $20 20 / 50 = 0.40 0.40 = 40%


